01:14:31,985 --> 01:14:34,146
Talked to mystery man yet?

788
01:14:35,589 --> 01:14:37,420
He never came back.

789
01:14:39,326 --> 01:14:40,918
Silly bugger.

790
01:14:47,033 --> 01:14:48,694
(door opens)

791
01:14:54,774 --> 01:14:56,799
I'm not asleep.

792
01:15:00,280 --> 01:15:02,111
Did you watch the news?

793
01:15:03,216 --> 01:15:04,808
Yeah.

794
01:15:06,186 --> 01:15:07,585
Will you find her?

795
01:15:09,422 --> 01:15:11,117
It's not looking good.

796
01:15:15,896 --> 01:15:18,296
I saw her client list,
Sonja.

797
01:15:20,533 --> 01:15:22,262
Why didn't you tell me?

798
01:15:28,508 --> 01:15:31,568
Because it was private.

799
01:15:34,281 --> 01:15:36,841
It was just something
I had to do.

800
01:15:40,220 --> 01:15:43,383
There was a time when there was
no private between you and me.

801
01:16:06,513 --> 01:16:09,482
That is because I had somebody
I could talk to.

802
01:16:09,549 --> 01:16:11,676
- I have to tell you something...
- I have to tell you...

803
01:16:11,751 --> 01:16:13,582
I had an affair.

804
01:16:21,161 --> 01:16:23,459
I slept with her twice.

805
01:16:27,701 --> 01:16:30,864
I know it hurts you.

806
01:16:30,937 --> 01:16:32,564
It hurts her...

807
01:16:37,544 --> 01:16:38,977
Why?

808
01:16:42,082 --> 01:16:43,709
Because I'm numb.

809
01:16:46,820 --> 01:16:49,152
I can't feel
anything anymore.

810
01:16:53,159 --> 01:16:55,218
Just totally
fucking numb.

811
01:17:09,843 --> 01:17:11,674
Why did you sleep
on the couch?

812
01:17:11,745 --> 01:17:15,340
I came in late last night.
I didn't want to wake your mama.

813
01:17:17,450 --> 01:17:18,917
Are you fighting?

814
01:17:20,854 --> 01:17:23,914
- Yeah, a bit.
- Boy: Why?

815
01:17:24,991 --> 01:17:27,619
There's something
we've got to sort out.

816
01:17:27,694 --> 01:17:30,424
- You all right, Mom?
- Yeah.

817
01:17:33,066 --> 01:17:34,624
I'll be in the car.

818
01:17:37,170 --> 01:17:40,628
Can you grab something to eat?
We're running late.

819
01:17:47,680 --> 01:17:50,012
Are we gonna
talk about this?

820
01:17:50,083 --> 01:17:53,519
Or you just going to punish me?
This is how you're gonna punish me?

821
01:17:54,854 --> 01:17:56,344
I fucked up.

822
01:17:56,423 --> 01:17:59,221
- People fuck up.
- Really? I don't.

823
01:17:59,292 --> 01:18:03,388
You know what's so easy?
It's easy to go and find somebody.

824
01:18:03,463 --> 01:18:07,729
You know what's hard?
What's hard is not to.

825
01:18:07,801 --> 01:18:09,792
Sonja, listen.
I just want...

826
01:18:09,869 --> 01:18:11,700
Get off me.

827
01:18:11,771 --> 01:18:13,705
God.

828
01:18:13,773 --> 01:18:17,106
We'll talk about this
tonight, all right?

829
01:18:17,177 --> 01:18:19,509
Oh... get fucked!

830
01:18:19,579 --> 01:18:22,013
I don't even know
if I'll be here later.

831
01:18:32,992 --> 01:18:34,254
Hi.

832
01:18:35,595 --> 01:18:37,324
Did you know?

833
01:19:00,620 --> 01:19:01,644
You're ready?

834
01:19:58,044 --> 01:19:59,477
Pete?

835
01:19:59,546 --> 01:20:01,241
It's me.

836
01:20:02,949 --> 01:20:04,974
Can you come over?

837
01:20:16,462 --> 01:20:19,124
- What number is it?
- 406.

838
01:20:27,073 --> 01:20:28,870
You sure
you're up to this?

839
01:20:32,979 --> 01:20:34,378
Mr. Phelan.

840
01:20:34,447 --> 01:20:37,211
We're investigating the disappearance
of Valerie Somers.

841
01:20:37,283 --> 01:20:39,274
We were hoping
you could help us.

842
01:20:41,588 --> 01:20:44,421
It's not a good time.
(clears his throat)

843
01:20:45,491 --> 01:20:47,721
- Patrick: I was out late.
- Who with?

844
01:20:48,995 --> 01:20:51,896
Mr. Phelan,
the woman's missing.

845
01:21:03,343 --> 01:21:06,335
- You know what's happened to her?
- Not yet.

846
01:21:06,412 --> 01:21:09,643
You had an appointment with her?
Can you tell us how she was?

847
01:21:11,517 --> 01:21:14,645
She seemed all right.
I don't know.

848
01:21:14,721 --> 01:21:16,245
You don't know?

849
01:21:16,322 --> 01:21:20,588
She's the therapist.
I wasn't focused on how she was.

850
01:21:20,660 --> 01:21:22,321
How do you
get along with her?

851
01:21:22,395 --> 01:21:25,057
- Fine.
- Leon: That's it?

852
01:21:25,131 --> 01:21:26,564
Fine?

853
01:21:29,535 --> 01:21:32,197
We didn't end our last session
on very good terms.

854
01:21:32,272 --> 01:21:34,137
Leon:
Why is that?

855
01:21:34,207 --> 01:21:36,767
- We disagreed about something.
- What was that?

856
01:21:36,843 --> 01:21:39,812
What? That guy
you've been fucking?

857
01:21:39,879 --> 01:21:42,473
- Leon: Married guy?
- How did you know about that?

858
01:21:42,548 --> 01:21:44,948
- She records all her sessions.
- That's private...

859
01:21:45,018 --> 01:21:48,510
- Yes, but under the circumstances...
- That's my life!

860
01:21:51,491 --> 01:21:53,220
Is there somebody
in that room?

861
01:21:53,293 --> 01:21:55,523
Who is it?
Your boyfriend?

862
01:21:55,595 --> 01:21:59,053
- Could you ask him to come out?
- He has nothing...

863
01:21:59,132 --> 01:22:00,326
- Leon!
- What's the matter with you?

864
01:22:00,400 --> 01:22:02,300
- You don't have the right...
- Who are you?!

865
01:22:02,368 --> 01:22:04,461
You have
no fucking right!

866
01:22:13,179 --> 01:22:14,612
Finished?

867
01:22:23,122 --> 01:22:24,783
That went well.

868
01:22:24,857 --> 01:22:27,348
Your marriage is falling apart
and so are you.

869
01:22:27,427 --> 01:22:31,261
- It's none of your business.
- It is if you can't do your job!

870
01:22:31,331 --> 01:22:33,697
If you don't like the way
I'm handling things,

871
01:22:33,766 --> 01:22:35,757
take it up at the station.

872
01:22:35,835 --> 01:22:37,769
Push.

873
01:23:25,418 --> 01:23:28,046
- (dialing)
- (ringing)

874
01:23:29,122 --> 01:23:30,783
(phone ringing)

875
01:23:33,826 --> 01:23:35,384
- Hello?
- Leon: Dylan?

876
01:23:35,461 --> 01:23:36,393
Hi, Dad.

877
01:23:38,498 --> 01:23:40,625
Could I speak to your mom?

878
01:23:43,403 --> 01:23:45,701
No, she's still
pissed off at you.

879
01:23:47,907 --> 01:23:49,602
All right.

880
01:23:49,675 --> 01:23:51,666
Tell her...

881
01:23:52,745 --> 01:23:55,680
- tell her I'll be home soon.
- All right. See you, Dad.

882
01:23:58,084 --> 01:23:59,574
What did he say?

883
01:24:01,220 --> 01:24:04,621
He said that he's sorry,
that he loves you,

884
01:24:04,690 --> 01:24:07,420
and he wants you to stop
being angry with him.

885
01:24:34,620 --> 01:24:36,850
You look bereft, Leon.

886
01:24:36,923 --> 01:24:38,948
The other question is,
why don't you?

887
01:24:41,461 --> 01:24:43,861
Don't be deceived
by appearances.

888
01:24:43,930 --> 01:24:45,795
Want a whiskey?

889
01:24:52,038 --> 01:24:54,506
Leon: Somebody
may have hurt your wife.

890
01:24:54,574 --> 01:24:57,941
- I need to know if it was you.
- I didn't hurt her.

891
01:24:58,010 --> 01:25:00,240
- She was upset on the phone.
- She was afraid.

892
01:25:00,313 --> 01:25:02,304
- Of what?
- Of being alone.

893
01:25:02,381 --> 01:25:05,077
Of me not being
there for her.

894
01:25:05,151 --> 01:25:06,778
Why weren't you
there for her?

895
01:25:10,990 --> 01:25:13,925
While your wife
was in some phone box,

896
01:25:13,993 --> 01:25:17,759
calling for your help,
where were you?

897
01:25:19,131 --> 01:25:21,156
Are you seeing someone else?

898
01:25:21,234 --> 01:25:23,259
- Is it an affair?
- No.

899
01:25:23,336 --> 01:25:25,270
With a man?
Is that what's going on?

900
01:25:25,338 --> 01:25:28,899
I believe that's what
Valerie thought was going on.

901
01:25:28,975 --> 01:25:30,602
What are you
talking about?

902
01:25:30,676 --> 01:25:34,612
For some reason, she believe
you were involved with Patrick Phelan.

903
01:25:34,680 --> 01:25:38,013
Is that it?
Were you seeing men on the side?

904
01:25:38,084 --> 01:25:40,177
- I don't have to listen to this?
- Yes, you do.

905
01:25:40,253 --> 01:25:42,653
My wife's out there somewhere.
What are you doing about it?

906
01:25:42,722 --> 01:25:44,622
I'm trying to find her.

907
01:25:44,690 --> 01:25:47,056
But I need to know
what's inside her head.

908
01:25:47,126 --> 01:25:48,923
I don't know.

909
01:25:52,064 --> 01:25:53,827
I don't know.

910
01:26:00,006 --> 01:26:02,099
Have you ever
cheated on your wife?

911
01:26:06,145 --> 01:26:07,373
No.

912
01:26:07,446 --> 01:26:10,643
- Never desired another woman?
- Yes, of course.

913
01:26:10,716 --> 01:26:12,274
- But you never acted on it?
- No.

914
01:26:12,351 --> 01:26:14,751
Well, you're
a better man than I am.

915
01:26:15,821 --> 01:26:17,448
So there is someone else?

916
01:26:17,523 --> 01:26:19,320
No.

917
01:26:20,826 --> 01:26:23,090
There was someone once.

918
01:26:23,162 --> 01:26:24,686
A woman.

919
01:26:25,998 --> 01:26:29,525
Once that's happened, you're never
entirely believed again.

920
01:26:29,602 --> 01:26:31,627
Something gets broken,

921
01:26:31,704 --> 01:26:34,264
permanently.
Trust, I suppose.

922
01:26:34,340 --> 01:26:37,309
When that happens,
anything's possible, it would seem.

923
01:26:41,013 --> 01:26:44,710
You don't lose a daughter,
like we lost Eleanor,

924
01:26:45,785 --> 01:26:47,719
without some damage.

925
01:26:49,789 --> 01:26:51,689
So where were you?

926
01:26:54,961 --> 01:26:57,088
I left work late.

927
01:26:59,298 --> 01:27:03,200
I stopped at the place
where my daughter was killed.

928
01:27:03,269 --> 01:27:06,204
I go there... a lot.

929
01:27:08,040 --> 01:27:11,976
- Valerie didn't know that.
- You didn't tell her?

930
01:27:13,646 --> 01:27:15,477
Why not, John?

931
01:27:23,856 --> 01:27:26,347
What holds
your marriage together, Leon?

932
01:27:34,533 --> 01:27:35,830
Loyalty?

933
01:27:36,902 --> 01:27:37,869
Love?

934
01:27:39,839 --> 01:27:42,831
Maybe habits sometimes,
passion, our kids.

935
01:27:46,512 --> 01:27:49,037
Ours was held together
by grief.

936
01:27:51,050 --> 01:27:53,712
There wasn't
much else left.

937
01:27:54,787 --> 01:27:56,550
You didn't love her
anymore?

938
01:27:56,622 --> 01:28:01,321
I'm saying that sometimes,
love isn't enough.

939
01:28:11,737 --> 01:28:13,068
Claudia: Leon!

940
01:28:13,139 --> 01:28:14,572
Where the hell
have you been?

941
01:28:14,640 --> 01:28:17,905
We got a call from a man,
saying his wife saw a neighbor

942
01:28:17,977 --> 01:28:21,413
throw a shoe into a vacant lot
on the night Valerie disappeared.

943
01:28:21,480 --> 01:28:23,812
She's got the shoe.
Black leather.

944
01:28:23,883 --> 01:28:25,851
Where are we going?

945
01:28:34,927 --> 01:28:37,555
- This could be tricky.
- Why?

946
01:28:39,198 --> 01:28:40,927
I know the woman.

947
01:28:41,000 --> 01:28:42,695
Oh Jesus!

948
01:28:49,842 --> 01:28:51,332
(knocking on door)

949
01:28:53,412 --> 01:28:56,210
- Detective Claudia Weis.
- Leon!

950
01:28:57,283 --> 01:28:59,979
- We had a drink the other night.
- How are you?

951
01:29:00,052 --> 01:29:01,019
Good.

952
01:29:01,087 --> 01:29:03,248
You'd better come in.
My wife's pretty upset.

953
01:29:10,096 --> 01:29:12,326
Pete: Jane, it's the police.

954
01:29:12,398 --> 01:29:15,162
- This is Leon and...
- Claudia.

955
01:29:15,234 --> 01:29:17,099
- and Claudia. Jane.
- Is that the shoe?

956
01:29:17,169 --> 01:29:19,137
Yeah.

957
01:29:20,272 --> 01:29:23,139
You shouldn't have touched the shoe,

958
01:29:23,209 --> 01:29:24,904
- Mrs...?
- O'May.

959
01:29:24,977 --> 01:29:26,968
It's Jane O'May.

960
01:29:27,046 --> 01:29:29,105
Right, Mrs. O'May,
you shouldn't have touched it.

961
01:29:30,182 --> 01:29:31,376
Well, I did.

962
01:29:32,518 --> 01:29:35,112
Yeah, but you shouldn't have.

963
01:29:35,187 --> 01:29:37,678
Well, I did, didn't I?

964
01:29:37,757 --> 01:29:39,418
It's on the table.

965
01:29:40,493 --> 01:29:43,155
- Could we have some coffee?
- Yeah.

966
01:29:43,229 --> 01:29:45,026
It's out
the back here. Thanks.

967
01:29:45,097 --> 01:29:46,997
I'll give you a hand.

968
01:30:03,582 --> 01:30:05,243
(whispering)
Are you all right?

969
01:30:08,721 --> 01:30:11,986
- Have you got a light?
- Yeah.

970
01:30:17,029 --> 01:30:18,826
How do you want to handle this?

971
01:30:21,567 --> 01:30:23,467
You're a policeman, aren't you?

972
01:30:23,536 --> 01:30:25,766
Why don't you just do your job?

973
01:30:27,173 --> 01:30:29,004
I've never seen you before.

974
01:30:34,747 --> 01:30:37,045
Nik:
Can I speak to Paula, please?

975
01:30:39,118 --> 01:30:40,642
Nik: It's urgent.

976
01:30:40,719 --> 01:30:43,483
Can you tell her to
call me as soon as she can?

977
01:30:43,556 --> 01:30:45,615
Yes, as soon as she can, please.

978
01:30:49,595 --> 01:30:51,358
(knocking on door)

979
01:30:51,430 --> 01:30:53,330
Leave it!
Go get your brother.

980
01:30:59,371 --> 01:31:02,363
Nik D'Amato? Detective
Claudia Weis, City Central.

981
01:31:02,441 --> 01:31:05,842
My kids. I need
someone to watch my kids.

982
01:31:08,280 --> 01:31:10,805
Right. I'll give you
a couple of minutes.

983
01:31:17,590 --> 01:31:19,888
Jane: So I go to the window,

984
01:31:19,959 --> 01:31:21,586
at about 11:30.

985
01:31:21,660 --> 01:31:24,185
I go to the window,
and he's chucking that.

986
01:31:24,263 --> 01:31:26,493
and he threw it over there,

987
01:31:26,565 --> 01:31:28,897
and he was looking
like he was...

988
01:31:28,968 --> 01:31:31,095
really guilty.

989
01:31:50,623 --> 01:31:52,352
(knocking on door)

990
01:31:52,424 --> 01:31:54,415
Nik.

991
01:31:54,493 --> 01:31:56,222
Nik: You're back, Pete?

992
01:31:57,429 --> 01:31:59,158
Only sort of.

993
01:32:00,399 --> 01:32:03,596
- How are you?
- Good. And you?

994
01:32:04,670 --> 01:32:06,331
I'm in a bit of trouble.

995
01:32:07,406 --> 01:32:10,034
Can you take the kids?

996
01:32:10,109 --> 01:32:11,701
Just till Paula gets back.

997
01:32:14,280 --> 01:32:16,942
Nik: I wouldn't ask
unless I really needed help.

998
01:32:22,888 --> 01:32:25,288
We'll take them.

999
01:32:25,357 --> 01:32:27,154
Thanks.

1000
01:32:27,226 --> 01:32:29,126
Here you go.

1001
01:32:30,296 --> 01:32:31,661
Nik: Thanks.

1002
01:32:32,731 --> 01:32:36,565
There's pajamas, toothbrush...

1003
01:32:36,635 --> 01:32:39,570
there's a video and some
other stuff in there as well.

1004
01:32:40,706 --> 01:32:42,264
Thanks very much, okay?

1005
01:32:42,341 --> 01:32:44,172
It's time to go.

1006
01:32:44,243 --> 01:32:47,041
No, Daddy, don't go.
Don't go!

1007
01:32:47,112 --> 01:32:49,876
Come on.
I'll be back soon.

1008
01:32:49,949 --> 01:32:52,611
- Come on.
- No! No!

1009
01:32:57,890 --> 01:33:00,552
How did you get the
scratches on your face?

1010
01:33:02,861 --> 01:33:05,887
- I want to see my wife.
- She's on her way.

1011
01:33:09,501 --> 01:33:12,061
Can you tell us where
you were Friday night?

1012
01:33:13,138 --> 01:33:14,867
I want to see Paula.

1013
01:33:14,940 --> 01:33:17,306
You are in deep shit, mate.

1014
01:33:17,376 --> 01:33:19,173
Your wife can't help you.

1015
01:33:20,479 --> 01:33:23,004
- Do I know you?
- I doubt it.

1016
01:33:24,383 --> 01:33:27,147
- I've seen you before.
- Shut up! Shut up!

1017
01:33:33,392 --> 01:33:36,293
- You were next door at Jane's place.
- I told you to shut up!

1018
01:33:45,437 --> 01:33:47,302
Where are my kids?

1019
01:33:47,373 --> 01:33:49,967
- Where are my bloody kids?!
- With your neighbor.

1020
01:33:50,042 --> 01:33:51,805
- Who are you?
- Calm down.

1021
01:33:51,877 --> 01:33:55,313
- I don't want to be calm.
- Can I get you something?

1022
01:33:55,381 --> 01:33:57,406
Yes, you can get
me my husband.

1023
01:33:57,483 --> 01:34:00,316
- And get me out of here!
- Can you just step in here?

1024
01:34:09,028 --> 01:34:10,893
Mrs. D'Amato.

1025
01:34:10,963 --> 01:34:14,194
I'm Detective Sergeant Zat.

1026
01:34:14,266 --> 01:34:17,099
I believe you met
Detective Constable Weis.

1027
01:34:18,203 --> 01:34:19,830
I want to see Nik.

1028
01:34:20,906 --> 01:34:23,204
Your husband is helping us
with our inquiries.

1029
01:34:23,275 --> 01:34:25,106
Bullshit.

1030
01:34:26,845 --> 01:34:29,871
He was seen throwing a shoe
into a vacant lot.

1031
01:34:31,683 --> 01:34:33,310
Who saw him?

1032
01:34:33,385 --> 01:34:37,719
A search was conducted
in the block opposite your house.

1033
01:34:38,957 --> 01:34:40,083
Mmm?

1034
01:34:40,159 --> 01:34:41,592
Another one?

1035
01:34:41,660 --> 01:34:45,187
My kids play there.
Every kid on the street plays there.

1036
01:34:46,265 --> 01:34:48,096
They found the shoe.

1037
01:34:48,167 --> 01:34:51,364
It was identified as belonging
to Ms. Valerie Somers.

1038
01:34:51,437 --> 01:34:54,167
She's been missing
since last Friday night.

1039
01:35:02,114 --> 01:35:03,911
Paula!

1040
01:35:11,190 --> 01:35:15,149
- Jane: Hello?
- Janey, it's Paula.

1041
01:35:15,227 --> 01:35:16,694
Hi.

1042
01:35:18,097 --> 01:35:19,724
Paula: Is Andrew awake?

1043
01:35:19,798 --> 01:35:22,062
Your kids are fine.

1044
01:35:22,134 --> 01:35:25,297
- You know?
- Maybe I could talk to Hannah.

1045
01:35:25,370 --> 01:35:28,339
Jane: No, she's asleep.

1046
01:35:28,407 --> 01:35:32,503
- Paula: The baby?
- You know what? They're all asleep.

1047
01:35:33,912 --> 01:35:36,005
Sorry about this, Janey.

1048
01:35:37,749 --> 01:35:39,944
Nik's in trouble.

1049
01:35:40,018 --> 01:35:43,215
