- Baby Panadol.

1073
01:38:21,380 --> 01:38:23,405
- What?
- Baby Panadol.

1074
01:38:23,482 --> 01:38:27,475
- You'll have to go to the chemist's.
- There's some at our house.

1075
01:38:52,110 --> 01:38:54,305
I'd met some mates for a drink.

1076
01:38:54,379 --> 01:38:57,974
We used to work together.
It's something we keep up.

1077
01:39:00,385 --> 01:39:03,877
We drank more than we should have,
so I took the backroad.

1078
01:39:04,956 --> 01:39:07,447
The police don't patrol it.

1079
01:39:09,795 --> 01:39:12,093
It must have been about...

1080
01:39:12,164 --> 01:39:14,064
a quarter to 12:00...

1081
01:39:15,901 --> 01:39:19,302
and I see this woman standing
at the side of the road.

1082
01:39:19,371 --> 01:39:21,362
I don't want to stop.

1083
01:39:21,440 --> 01:39:25,399
It's late, and I'm thinking
Paula will get worried.

1084
01:39:25,477 --> 01:39:28,207
But what do I do?
The woman needs help.

1085
01:39:28,280 --> 01:39:29,474
So I pull over.

1086
01:39:31,616 --> 01:39:33,607
My car ran off the road.

1087
01:39:35,821 --> 01:39:36,845
Get in.

1088
01:39:44,796 --> 01:39:46,354
Thanks.

1089
01:39:52,537 --> 01:39:54,198
What's your name?

1090
01:39:55,907 --> 01:39:56,965
Valerie.

1091
01:39:57,042 --> 01:39:58,737
I'm Nik.

1092
01:40:02,180 --> 01:40:05,581
Nik: It turns out she lives
in one of those houses by the Bay.

1093
01:40:05,650 --> 01:40:08,141
There's a string
of houses along there.

1094
01:40:08,220 --> 01:40:11,451
It's out of my way.
It's in the opposite direction.

1095
01:40:12,524 --> 01:40:14,617
She doesn't say much.

1096
01:40:14,693 --> 01:40:16,456
I can tell she doesn't want
to talk, so I just...

1097
01:40:16,528 --> 01:40:17,927
leave it.

1098
01:40:24,035 --> 01:40:25,696
But I know this shortcut

1099
01:40:25,771 --> 01:40:29,138
and I just don't...
I just don't think.

1100
01:40:33,011 --> 01:40:36,174
And before I can say,
"This is the short way,"

1101
01:40:36,248 --> 01:40:38,079
